{{Infobox person | name = Georgina Burnett | image = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1978|12|7|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Sydney]], [[Australia]] | residence = [[Sevenoaks]], [[Kent]], [[United Kingdom]] | occupation = Weather presenter, TV presenter, TV producer, vlogger, life coach, property developer | spouse = | children = | website = {{URL|https://www.georginaburnett.com}} | footnotes = }}
'''Georgina Burnett''' (born 7 December 1978) is an Australian-born British-Polynesian [[weather presenter]], [[television presenter]], [[Vlog|vlogger]], [[Real estate development|property developer]] and [[life coach]].
==Early life== Georgina Burnett was born on 7 December 1978 in [[Sydney]], [[Australia]]. At three years old, her family moved to the [[United Kingdom]], settling in [[Dorset]]. She has 3 brothers.<ref name="southeastbusiness">{{cite web |title=A sunny nature {{!}} South East Business |url=http://www.southeastbusiness.com/section/features/a-sunny-nature |website=www.southeastbusiness.com |accessdate=16 July 2018 |language=en}}</ref>
==Career== Burnett currently freelances as a weather presenter and news reporter for all the UK nations and regions, most commonly [[BBC London News]], [[BBC Scotland]], [[BBC Cymru Wales]], [[BBC Northern Ireland]], [[South East Today|BBC South East Today]], [[BBC Look East]], and [[South Today|BBC South Today]], and also presents the weather for a number of BBC regional radio stations.<ref name="southeastbusiness"/>
Burnett is a DIY and interior design enthusiast and has been investing in and developing properties since 2009. One of her properties was featured in [[25 Beautiful Homes]]. She shares her knowledge and ideas through her blog and online channel ''The Home Genie''.<ref name="metro">{{cite web |title=TV presenter Georgina Burnett loves renovating houses, the more dilapidated the better |url=https://www.metro.news/tv-presenter-georgina-burnett-loves-renovating-houses-the-more-dilapidated-the-better/1058579/ |website=Metro Newspaper UK |accessdate=16 July 2018}}</ref>
She has also written expert advice for [[The Sunday Times]], [[The Sunday Telegraph]], [[The Guardian]], [[The Independent]], 25 Beautiful Homes and a number of other interiors magazines.<ref>{{cite web |title=Georgina Burnett - Life Coaching |url=http://www.footprintcoaching.org.uk/georgina.html |website=www.footprintcoaching.org.uk}}</ref>
