{{Infobox Organization |name = Washington Federation of Independent Schools |image = WFIS.png |image_border = |size = 150px |caption = |map = |msize = |mcaption = |abbreviation = WFIS |motto = |formation = February 12, 1969<ref>[http://www.wfis.org/HTML/WinterDinner09.htm 40th anniversary]</ref> |extinction = |type = [[Non-governmental organization]] |status = |purpose = [[Educational accreditation]] |headquarters = |location = |region_served = [[Washington (U.S. state)|Washington State]] |membership = |language = |leader_title = Executive director |leader_name = Suzie Hanson |main_organ = |parent_organization = [[Council of American Private Education]] |affiliations = [[ Northwest Association of Independent Schools]] |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = [http://www.wfis.org wfis.org] |remarks = }}
The '''Washington Federation of Independent Schools''' ('''WFIS''') is an [[umbrella organization]] of [[private school|private]] and [[independent school]]s in the [[United States|U.S.]] state of [[Washington (U.S. state)|Washington]], informally representing Washington in the [[Washington State Office of Private Education|Office of Private Education]].<ref name=wfis>[http://www.wfis.org/ WFIS homepage]</ref>
==Purpose== As laid out by the executives of the federation, the goals of WFIS are:<ref>[http://www.wfis.org/ WFIS speaks as a voice on behalf of its members]</ref>
#To promote the vital role of private schools in [[Education in Washington|Washington education]] and their significant contributions to educating the public and promoting the common good. #To promote the rights of parents to educate their children in the schools of their choice. #To encourage excellence and pluralism in education, and to promote the rights of private schools to fulfill their unique missions. #To foster the participation of the private school community in shaping the state's education agenda, and to develop and promote positions on educational policy. #To assure equitable access to all services to which private schools are entitled, while allowing them to maintain their independence.
